Structural Enforcement Mechanism:
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
The component is mathematically incapable of rendering an absolute currency value.

1. No scalar "total" prop exists — total is ALWAYS computed as [indexLow, indexHigh]
2. Every segment REQUIRES paired indices [indexLow, indexHigh] — no point estimates allowed
3. Every segment REQUIRES disclaimerId (non-optional) — TypeScript error without it
4. The render path ALWAYS outputs: "[low, high] — <disclaimer>"

An absolute number cannot be instantiated at the type level. This is not a prompt guard.
This is not a runtime check. This is an architectural property enforced by TypeScript's
type system. No prop, no field, no code path exists to accept or render a scalar price.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

